Section Goals
  -Table Basics: <table>, <tr>, <td>, and <th> **CRUCIAL**
  -Table Sections: <thead>, <tfoot>, <tbody> **Important**
  -Table Colspan and Rowspan **Nice To Have**
  -Form Element Basics **CRUCIAL**
  -Button Elements **CRUCIAL**
  -Labels **CRUCIAL**
  -Range & Text Areas **Important**
  -Common Input Types **CRUCIAL**
  -Form Validations **Important**


HTML Tables Elements
<table>
<td> - defines a cell of a table that contains data
<tr> - represents a row of cells in a table
<th> - defines a header of a group of table cells

<thead> - can have more than one row of header
<tfoot>

rowspan
colspan

HTML FORMS
-creating FORMS
  the <form> element itseself is a shell or container that doesnt have any visual impact
  we then fill the form with a collection of inputs, checkboxes, buttons, etc
  i.e: email, fullname, password and confirm password

  -represents a document section containing interactive controls for submitting information
  -the action attribute specifies where the form data should be section
  -the method attribute specifies which HTTP method should be used